other_tests.findings: A 2.5 x 2.0 hypodense exophytic lesion arising from the interpolar region of the left kidney is consistent with a simple renal cyst and stable in size. No renal or ureteral stones are identified. There is no hydronephrosis or hydroureter. A 1.7 x 2.6 cm soft tissue lesion identified in the deep right inguinal region, underlying the right inguinal hernia repair site, is similar compared to the prior MRI. Lung bases demonstrate bilateral, plate-like atelectasis.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The soft tissue lesion in the right inguinal region is similar compared to the prior MRI. The renal cyst is noted to be stable in size.
